POLICE and fire services are investigating the cause of a fire at a block of flats in Parkwood which killed a man and left seven people homeless in the early hours of Monday morning.  The City of Cape Town’s fire and rescue spokesperson, Jermaine Carelse, said they were alerted to the blaze shortly before 2am. Carelse said the entire flat on the first floor was damaged and the team of firefighters from Wynberg, Ottery and Epping responded the scene. “The fire was extinguished at 03:26am and the scene was handed over to SAPS,” he said. The cause of the fire is yet to be determined.. Police spokesperson Sergeant Wesley Twigg confirmed that Grassy Park SAPS registered an inquest docket for investigation and that one adult male was declared deceased at the scene.  “The circumstances surrounding the death of a 44-year-old male, following a fire in Viljoen Walk, Parkwood, (on Monday) at about 01:55 am are under investigation. “According to reports the victim was asleep when the fire broke out. The victim was declared deceased on the scene by medical personnel,” said Twigg. A community activist and a founder of Parkwood Community Upliftment, Max Amansure expressed her condolences and said her organisation had provided food parcels and toiletries to the affected families. Anyone with any information about this incident can contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111.